Dewey & LeBoeuf Hires Former Stephenson Harwood Energy Head Marc Hammerson

-- B y   C u l l e n   W h e a t l e y
-- 
2011-10-03T15:02:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-03/dewey-leboeuf-hires-former-stephenson-harwood-energy-head-marc-hammerson.html
(Corrects lawyer’s title based on firm’s clarification in
headline and first paragraph.)  Dewey & LeBoeuf LLP hired Marc
Hammerson, formerly of London-based Stephenson Harwood Ltd.’s
energy group, to be a partner in its project finance and
infrastructure practice.  “He has advised on projects around the world, so he is a
perfect fit for our global practice,” John LaMaster, the head
of New York-based Dewey & LeBoeuf’s oil-and-gas sector group,
said today in an e-mailed statement.  Hammerson has worked on mergers and acquisitions,  project
financing  and private-equity investment on projects in the
 Middle East , Southeast Asia and  Africa , according to the
statement. He will be based in the London office.  His hiring is the eighth the firm has made this year in its
global energy practice.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cullen Wheatley in New York at 
 cwheatley2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Hytha at   mhytha@bloomberg.net . 